HEADWORD: flabby
<hw>flab"by</hw> <pr>(fl⟦acr⟧b"b⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Flap</er>.]</ety> <def>Yielding to the touch, and easily moved or
shaken; hanging loose by its own weight; wanting firmness; flaccid;
<as>as, <ex>flabby</ex> flesh</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

